1
00:00:01,002 --> 00:00:07,725
Raise red, raise white,
don't lower red, lower white.

2
00:00:08,038 --> 00:00:14,530
Lower red, raise red,
raise white, lower white.

3
00:00:14,570 --> 00:00:19,410
Hey, wait!
Wasn't that weird just now?

4
00:00:19,450 --> 00:00:20,531
Funny face, right?

5
00:00:20,571 --> 00:00:22,601
Again?

6
00:00:22,641 --> 00:00:23,707
Funny face festival!

7
00:00:23,747 --> 00:00:26,574
- Fine, here we go. Ready?
- Funny face festival.

8
00:00:26,850 --> 00:00:32,000
Thanks to my routine, a brief peace had
settled over the Yanagida household,

9
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:37,000
but I still hadn't told Chika
about my great idea.

10
00:00:37,761 --> 00:00:39,622
Funny face!

11
00:00:39,662 --> 00:00:42,650
We're gonna make you pull a funny face!

12
00:00:43,778 --> 00:00:45,480
Do you think you can go, Taro?

13
00:00:45,876 --> 00:00:50,600
Don't force it. It's totally fine
if you can't go.

14
00:00:50,876 --> 00:00:56,256
Come on! They picked the flag-raising game,
and we practiced a ton.

15
00:00:56,296 --> 00:00:59,080
Don't force him to go.

16
00:00:59,143 --> 00:01:03,280
I'm not forcing him, but if he goes,
it'll boost his confidence.

17
00:01:03,550 --> 00:01:05,800
Taro, you decide. Either way is fine.

18
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:11,640
You've worked so hard already.
Even Mama's terrified of performing.

19
00:01:17,182 --> 00:01:18,720
No go, huh.

20
00:01:21,883 --> 00:01:23,773
Okay. I'll go.

21
00:01:25,364 --> 00:01:27,483
Wait, you will? Are you sure?

22
00:01:27,855 --> 00:01:31,560
If I don't go, there's no one
to call out the flag commands.

23
00:01:31,615 --> 00:01:36,625
That's right! Good boy, Taro.
You'll feel great once you do it.

24
00:01:37,610 --> 00:01:39,761
But don't come watch, okay?

25
00:01:39,801 --> 00:01:42,320
What? Why not? I wanna see!

26
00:01:42,490 --> 00:01:44,640
- I don't want it.
- It's fine, we won't go.

27
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:47,470
We're just happy
you're going to school at all.

28
00:01:47,510 --> 00:01:52,200
It's at the morning assembly, right?
It's time. Should I take you by bike?

29
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:54,441
No, I'm fine. I'll walk.

30
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:56,680
Okay. See you later!

31
00:02:04,746 --> 00:02:06,400
Wait, we're really not going?

32
00:02:07,926 --> 00:02:09,720
Oh please. Of course we're going.

33
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:16,119
He's embarrassed to be watched by you.
We'll sneak in and watch secretly.

34
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:17,920
Then let's hurry! Are we taking the bike?

35
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:20,880
Are you stupid? If we leave now,
we'll catch up to him!

36
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:23,859
Oh, right, right.
So let's go inside for now...

37
00:02:23,899 --> 00:02:26,100
Inside? No, hold on,
we just wait a bit, then go!

38
00:02:26,140 --> 00:02:27,640
How many minutes?

39
00:02:27,687 --> 00:02:29,441
Three, four, five minutes.

40
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,287
- Three, four, five minutes?
- Five minutes!

41
00:02:31,327 --> 00:02:32,880
- Okay.
- Let's go in five.

42
00:02:33,239 --> 00:02:34,960
Hey, calm down. Close it, close it.

43
00:02:43,843 --> 00:02:45,909
Alright!

44
00:02:48,969 --> 00:02:50,169
Ta-da!

45
00:02:50,595 --> 00:02:52,361
Yay!

46
00:02:52,601 --> 00:02:54,048
Thank you!

47
00:02:56,988 --> 00:02:58,255
Here we go!

48
00:03:06,027 --> 00:03:08,920
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

49
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:38,456
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

50
00:03:39,102 --> 00:03:40,289
Episode 10: Married Manzai Duo

51
00:03:40,329 --> 00:03:44,560
I'm sorry you came all this way,
especially before work.

52
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:48,640
Well, I had a feeling this would happen.

53
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:53,006
But I really thought he could pull it off.

54
00:03:53,046 --> 00:03:58,446
It can't be helped. But I think
he's probably feeling pretty down.

55
00:03:58,486 --> 00:04:04,480
About running away at the last minute.
Please, look after him for us.

56
00:04:04,746 --> 00:04:09,800
Of course. I think it's wonderful
he made it as far as he did.

57
00:04:10,912 --> 00:04:13,725
Thank you. We'll be going now.

58
00:04:13,765 --> 00:04:15,160
Thank you.

59
00:04:24,976 --> 00:04:30,840
Hey, stop making that face. The teacher said
he did great just getting this far.

60
00:04:31,090 --> 00:04:32,241
You're expecting too much.

61
00:04:32,281 --> 00:04:36,360
I know, but I thought this was
a small step, you know...

62
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:39,150
A chance for him to build some confidence.

63
00:04:39,190 --> 00:04:41,880
It
was
a small step. More than enough.

64
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:45,960
Worry about yourself, alright?
You'd better show some results.

65
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:49,156
Also, hang out the futons to air.
And vacuum the bedroom.

66
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:50,683
Wait a sec!

67
00:04:50,949 --> 00:04:52,973
What? I'm running late here.

68
00:04:53,013 --> 00:04:55,213
No, um, well...

69
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,819
What?

70
00:04:56,912 --> 00:05:00,370
So, about those results you mentioned...

71
00:05:00,410 --> 00:05:02,670
Wait, do we have to talk about this now?

72
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:05,154
I have to get to work, unlike you.

73
00:05:05,194 --> 00:05:07,021
Fine, I'll say it in five seconds.

74
00:05:07,061 --> 00:05:08,960
- Make it two.
- Okay.

75
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,200
Um...

76
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,400
Will you form a manzai comedy duo with me?

77
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,033
Huh? What? Who?

78
00:05:17,073 --> 00:05:19,600
Me and you, Chika.

79
00:05:19,956 --> 00:05:22,557
What are you saying?
Are you stupid? Seriously.

80
00:05:22,751 --> 00:05:26,201
Wait, wait. Just hear me out.
I'll explain calmly.

81
00:05:26,241 --> 00:05:28,989
You know I've always been into comedy, right?

82
00:05:29,029 --> 00:05:34,233
Like I said before, we used to go
to comedy shows all the time.

83
00:05:34,273 --> 00:05:38,986
And you even said I was funnier
than Summers, remember?

84
00:05:39,026 --> 00:05:43,709
I never said that. And clinging
to past glories like that? It's pathetic.

85
00:05:43,749 --> 00:05:46,921
I'm not clinging to past glories or anything.

86
00:05:46,961 --> 00:05:50,960
Yes, you are! I complimented you. It's one
of the few things you can be proud of.

87
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,280
Fine, let's leave it at that then.

88
00:05:53,346 --> 00:06:00,526
So what if I make it big as a comedian first,
then break into film and TV from there?

89
00:06:00,566 --> 00:06:02,640
You know, like Takeshi.

90
00:06:02,856 --> 00:06:05,440
With manzai comedy, we only need two people.

91
00:06:05,589 --> 00:06:09,720
People from other fields make movies
all the time with zero talent.

92
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:14,400
You have zero talent, too!
Why do I have to be your manzai partner?

93
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:17,880
I just feel like it would
definitely work out with you, Chika.

94
00:06:18,049 --> 00:06:22,310
Plus, while helping Taro practice,
I realized something.

95
00:06:22,350 --> 00:06:26,376
Showing Taro that his parents take on
a manzai challenge could be

96
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:29,707
a really wonderful thing for him.

97
00:06:30,376 --> 00:06:35,481
You know that live venue
by the station? Marquee?

98
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:38,353
They do comedy shows there sometimes.

99
00:06:38,393 --> 00:06:45,240
We went to one when we moved here, remember?
That totally unfunny show.

100
00:06:45,637 --> 00:06:49,298
Remember, they had
an amateur segment? Do you recall that?

101
00:06:49,338 --> 00:06:54,483
What if we performed there a bunch
and built up a reputation?

102
00:06:56,783 --> 00:06:58,920
What do you think?

103
00:07:02,303 --> 00:07:06,360
Just hang out the futons to air.
Forget it, and you're dead.

104
00:07:13,073 --> 00:07:19,600
A married couple in their 40s debuting
in manzai might even go viral online.

105
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:26,000
These half-baked little delusions were
already creeping into my mind.

106
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:48,320
I'm home!

107
00:08:10,893 --> 00:08:12,131
Welcome back.

108
00:08:12,420 --> 00:08:13,688
Hi.

109
00:08:22,768 --> 00:08:25,205
How'd it go? Your school presentation.

110
00:08:26,281 --> 00:08:28,880
Hmm? Fine, I guess.

111
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,296
Did they laugh?

112
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,200
Yeah, sort of.

113
00:08:38,386 --> 00:08:40,560
Which part got laughs?

114
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,270
Huh?

115
00:08:45,226 --> 00:08:48,640
Did they really like it?
It's okay if they didn't.

116
00:08:49,546 --> 00:08:51,800
Hey, did you really do it?

117
00:08:52,566 --> 00:08:54,032
I'll watch this elsewhere.

118
00:09:07,647 --> 00:09:11,640
Taro, wanna go grocery shopping
for dinner with me?

119
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,000
No thanks.

120
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:34,440
I'm home!

121
00:09:38,209 --> 00:09:39,209
I'm back.

122
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,367
Welcome back.

123
00:09:40,407 --> 00:09:42,327
Huh? Where's Taro?

124
00:09:42,396 --> 00:09:46,080
Probably in the bedroom
or workroom, watching his iPad.

125
00:09:46,443 --> 00:09:49,881
You didn't say something stupid again,
did you? Like about his presentation.

126
00:09:49,921 --> 00:09:51,880
I didn't say anything.

127
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:54,013
You're always so pushy.

128
00:09:54,702 --> 00:09:58,283
Hey, the futons are still out.
Bring them in already.

129
00:09:58,323 --> 00:09:59,720
Oh, sorry, sorry.

130
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:02,840
Seriously, do what you're supposed to.

131
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:07,200
Taro! Taro, I'm home.

132
00:10:32,903 --> 00:10:33,910
Broccoli?

133
00:10:33,950 --> 00:10:36,716
Broccoli. Not cauliflower.

134
00:10:36,756 --> 00:10:38,120
Not cauliflower?

135
00:10:43,063 --> 00:10:45,560
It's growing out of his head!

136
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:49,480
Could it be...

137
00:11:02,303 --> 00:11:08,360
You were totally grilling Taro
about his comedy role, weren't you?

138
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:11,880
He says you're too pushy,
so he's staying over there.

139
00:11:11,963 --> 00:11:14,923
I just asked him casually.

140
00:11:15,196 --> 00:11:18,440
Seriously, stop it.
You're always so relentless.

141
00:11:19,576 --> 00:11:23,320
Also, about those results
you mentioned this morning.

142
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:24,970
Huh?

143
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:27,760
Don't "huh" me.
You're serious about this, right?

144
00:11:28,945 --> 00:11:30,650
Oh, this morning's topic.

145
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:33,000
That's what I said! God, you're annoying.

146
00:11:34,802 --> 00:11:36,080
I'm serious.

147
00:11:37,408 --> 00:11:42,480
You better be. Then actually commit to it.
Don't you dare bail.

148
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:44,760
I won't bail.

149
00:11:45,429 --> 00:11:47,240
Say it again. Louder.

150
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:52,000
I won't bail...

151
00:11:57,897 --> 00:11:59,440
Then fine, I'll do it.

152
00:11:59,923 --> 00:12:03,400
But you better come up
with a damn good routine.

153
00:12:03,829 --> 00:12:06,576
If it's something lame
like the flag-raising game, count me out.

154
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:19,166
Honestly, I was getting a little scared.

155
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:23,720
This willingness to commit is
what makes Chika amazing,

156
00:12:23,942 --> 00:12:26,200
and also incredibly reckless.

157
00:12:26,826 --> 00:12:30,720
When Chika makes up her mind,
her resolve is something else.

158
00:12:31,347 --> 00:12:38,160
Was forming a comedy duo really
the right path for us as a couple?

159
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:44,160
The more I thought about it, the more
an indescribable fear welled up inside me.

160
00:12:44,999 --> 00:12:46,120
Here.

161
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:47,926
Huh? Wait, what's this?

162
00:12:47,966 --> 00:12:50,360
Got it from a live venue.
I already signed us up.

163
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,606
Huh?

164
00:12:52,066 --> 00:12:54,080
November 10th? That's so soon!

165
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:57,360
You're serious about this, right?
Then sooner's better.

166
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:00,760
All right!

167
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:03,120
And if you write something boring,
I'll kill you.

168
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:22,080
I had no choice
but to start writing material for that show.

169
00:13:44,113 --> 00:13:47,340
We got married and formed a duo
as husband and wife,

170
00:13:47,380 --> 00:13:50,540
but we divorced four years ago,
so now we're a duo of total strangers.

171
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:52,400
Nice to meet you all!

172
00:13:53,172 --> 00:13:57,120
Wow, Dad, you've really gotten
into stand-up comedy, huh?

173
00:13:58,179 --> 00:14:02,480
Well, Dad ended up forming
a comedy duo with Mom.

174
00:14:02,492 --> 00:14:03,731
With Mom?

175
00:14:05,986 --> 00:14:07,466
Any ideas what we should do?

176
00:14:07,506 --> 00:14:10,320
Huh? Why not just do the flag-raising game?

177
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,900
That's a no-go, apparently.
Mom's so mean, right?

178
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:15,200
She said to write
something funnier than that.

179
00:14:16,380 --> 00:14:21,520
Then Mom's funny face! Make a funny face
and sing like Doburock. That'll be great!

180
00:14:22,039 --> 00:14:24,960
Yeah, but Daddy's a terrible singer.

181
00:14:25,054 --> 00:14:27,054
You're so picky.

182
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:30,240
Then dirty stuff.
Dirty jokes always get laughs.

183
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:32,040
Dirty stuff? Like what?

184
00:14:32,486 --> 00:14:34,000
You'd know, Dad.

185
00:14:35,087 --> 00:14:36,480
Well, yeah.

186
00:14:37,679 --> 00:14:39,993
Hey, if it flops,
can we join Doburock's fan club?

187
00:14:40,126 --> 00:14:44,320
The Doburock fan club
and this are two separate things.

188
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:47,440
But you're the one who asked me!

189
00:14:47,472 --> 00:14:51,640
I just asked what kind of stuff is good.
That's not the same thing.

190
00:14:57,929 --> 00:15:00,040
Dad, why are you smirking?

191
00:15:01,497 --> 00:15:03,481
I just thought of a funny routine.

192
00:15:05,423 --> 00:15:06,680
What? Tell me!

193
00:15:06,970 --> 00:15:08,320
No way.

194
00:15:09,470 --> 00:15:10,920
It's dirty, isn't it?

195
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,880
Yep.

196
00:15:28,306 --> 00:15:29,720
Huh? What?

197
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:31,440
I'm sorry.

198
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:34,506
Dad just came up with a funny routine.

199
00:15:34,546 --> 00:15:37,560
Ugh, it's gonna be lame again.
Just like the flag-raising game.

200
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,180
That was fun, though.

201
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:40,580
Yeah, it was fun.

202
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:42,140
How was that fun? It's just a game.

203
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:44,320
- Like the funny faces.
- Yeah, the funny faces.

204
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,680
That's not a routine.

205
00:15:45,828 --> 00:15:46,979
Funny face.

206
00:15:47,019 --> 00:15:48,019
Huh?

207
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:49,393
Funny face.

208
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:51,120
Why?

209
00:15:52,207 --> 00:15:53,781
Why do I have to do it?

210
00:15:53,821 --> 00:15:55,288
- Funny face.
- Funny face.

211
00:15:58,170 --> 00:15:59,380
C'mon, do it for real.

212
00:15:59,420 --> 00:16:02,364
Why would I do that for real
while we're eating? No way.

213
00:16:02,404 --> 00:16:04,706
- When you get the call, you gotta!
- Like this?

214
00:16:04,746 --> 00:16:07,530
The rule is you have to go all out.
No exceptions.

215
00:16:12,759 --> 00:16:14,960
Um, got a minute?

216
00:16:15,413 --> 00:16:18,993
You'd barge in even if I said no.
You never wait for consent.

217
00:16:19,399 --> 00:16:20,672
Sorry.

218
00:16:20,712 --> 00:16:25,240
So, I wrote some material.

219
00:16:26,574 --> 00:16:27,713
And?

220
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:30,680
I want you to look at it later.

221
00:16:30,954 --> 00:16:32,360
After Taro is asleep.

222
00:16:33,496 --> 00:16:35,720
If it's boring, I'm seriously not doing this.

223
00:16:37,494 --> 00:16:39,320
I'm not too confident either.

224
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,240
Please.

225
00:17:08,074 --> 00:17:09,881
What is this?
What's supposed to be funny?

226
00:17:09,921 --> 00:17:13,041
No, it's probably funny.
You were laughing too, Chika.

227
00:17:13,081 --> 00:17:17,766
I was laughing at how stupid it is.
This whole thing's riding on my funny face.

228
00:17:17,806 --> 00:17:22,513
Your funny faces make it good.
You don't see stuff like this, you know!

229
00:17:22,553 --> 00:17:27,160
How would I know? Unlike you,
I'm busy. No time to watch comedy.

230
00:17:29,414 --> 00:17:31,920
Wait, just a little.

231
00:17:32,682 --> 00:17:34,040
Just a bit.

232
00:17:34,413 --> 00:17:35,495
Hm?

233
00:17:35,535 --> 00:17:38,040
Wanna try running through it?

234
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:42,040
- Right now?
- Yeah. Just to try it.

235
00:17:50,754 --> 00:17:52,434
Hey there, everyone! I'm Tsumi!

236
00:17:52,474 --> 00:17:54,360
Hey there, everyone! I'm Batsu.

237
00:17:54,414 --> 00:17:57,720
Together, we're Dostoevsky!

238
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,321
This is kinda embarrassing.

239
00:17:59,361 --> 00:18:00,960
You can't be the one getting shy!

240
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:06,678
So, we're a husband-and-wife manzai duo
on the verge of breaking up...

241
00:18:06,718 --> 00:18:08,198
Let's make it married manzai.

242
00:18:08,238 --> 00:18:09,555
- Married manzai duo?
- Yeah.

243
00:18:09,595 --> 00:18:11,554
- Don't tell me what to say.
- It'll be better.

244
00:18:11,594 --> 00:18:15,801
We're a married manzai duo.
You came up with a funny bit today, right?

245
00:18:15,841 --> 00:18:16,987
Yep, nailed it.

246
00:18:17,027 --> 00:18:18,656
If it's boring, we're divorcing.

247
00:18:18,696 --> 00:18:24,061
Well, I'm confident this time. We are
actually suffering from a loss of libido.

248
00:18:24,101 --> 00:18:28,000
That's right. We don't just have
less of it, we lost it.

249
00:18:28,785 --> 00:18:30,024
Wait, is this necessary?

250
00:18:30,064 --> 00:18:33,360
- It's corny.
- No, a bit of corny stuff works, trust me.

251
00:18:33,633 --> 00:18:34,878
It's all corny, though.

252
00:18:34,918 --> 00:18:36,120
No, no.

253
00:18:36,226 --> 00:18:40,293
That's exactly why we, a couple
without libido, should do this routine.

254
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:41,800
Go on, let's hear it.

255
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:44,552
We each pick a celebrity we would sleep with

256
00:18:44,592 --> 00:18:47,180
and act out the faces and sounds
we'd make at the climax.

257
00:18:47,220 --> 00:18:48,481
Wait, what?

258
00:18:48,521 --> 00:18:51,281
You like Koichi Sato, right?

259
00:18:51,321 --> 00:18:57,494
You would act out the face and voice
right before you finish with Koichi Sato.

260
00:18:57,534 --> 00:19:00,400
Huh? What? Like this?

261
00:19:00,553 --> 00:19:05,200
I just did it with Koichi!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze.

262
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:09,320
Hey, will this really gonna get laughs?

263
00:19:09,653 --> 00:19:16,240
Well, today's just our first read-through,
so we can refine it from here.

264
00:19:16,789 --> 00:19:18,531
I put a lot of thought into this, you know.

265
00:19:18,571 --> 00:19:23,000
Like, maybe use his full name
instead of just "Koichi."

266
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,921
Sorry, I don't get it at all.

267
00:19:25,961 --> 00:19:29,960
You're more into the Kin-chan types,
so maybe this isn't your thing.

268
00:19:30,201 --> 00:19:36,040
Okay, Koichi Sato is fine,
but what's up with Bekako Katsura?

269
00:19:37,533 --> 00:19:40,280
I want Hugh or Ken Takakura.

270
00:19:40,313 --> 00:19:42,273
"Hugh?" Oh, you mean Hugh Grant?

271
00:19:42,313 --> 00:19:45,641
Yeah. And when will you stop
having a crush on Mitsu Dan?

272
00:19:45,681 --> 00:19:49,880
Hey, it's fine. It works better
if we pick people we actually like.

273
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:52,033
Wait, didn't you have a thing for Bekako?

274
00:19:52,073 --> 00:19:55,960
I like him, but not like that.
Plus, he goes by Master Nanko now.

275
00:19:57,780 --> 00:20:02,240
Anyway, I'm going to bed.
I've got a bad feeling about all this.

276
00:20:02,964 --> 00:20:06,480
Can't you write something else?
Something like Yasu & Kiyo?

277
00:20:07,877 --> 00:20:09,594
- Good night.
- Yeah, good night.

278
00:20:11,152 --> 00:20:16,440
Still, after Taro went to sleep,
Chika and I rehearsed night after night.

279
00:20:17,873 --> 00:20:23,560
I just did it with Hugh Grant!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze.

280
00:20:24,107 --> 00:20:27,128
You gotta do the funny face
on the "squeeze" part, or it won't land.

281
00:20:27,168 --> 00:20:30,179
Come on, I've only done it a few times,

282
00:20:30,219 --> 00:20:31,561
there's no way I can pull it off.

283
00:20:31,601 --> 00:20:33,611
No, I think that's a mindset thing.

284
00:20:33,651 --> 00:20:35,494
It's fine, we're just practicing.

285
00:20:35,534 --> 00:20:37,840
No, you're holding back right now.

286
00:20:37,954 --> 00:20:42,346
I don't need comments from you.
You try it yourself.

287
00:20:42,386 --> 00:20:45,926
- No, it's your bit now.
- You should do it, too.

288
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:50,960
I just did it with Jennifer Lawrence!
Oh no...

289
00:20:52,499 --> 00:20:54,000
Why are you embarrassed?

290
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,173
That was weak. So lame.

291
00:20:56,209 --> 00:20:58,520
I just did it with Shohei Hino...
Wait, it was Shohei Uno.

292
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:01,241
I just did it with Shohei Uno.

293
00:21:01,281 --> 00:21:04,393
So cute, I can't even...

294
00:21:04,433 --> 00:21:05,433
What's this?

295
00:21:05,470 --> 00:21:07,761
This makes no sense. "So cute, I can't even!'

296
00:21:07,801 --> 00:21:10,200
I was just writing from your perspective.

297
00:21:10,346 --> 00:21:11,800
You so don't get it.

298
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:18,806
Oh my God, I just did it with Koichi Sato!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze.

299
00:21:18,846 --> 00:21:21,566
But yeah, Koichi Sato really gets me going.

300
00:21:21,606 --> 00:21:23,961
It does feel different when you say his name.

301
00:21:24,001 --> 00:21:25,158
Love matters, huh.

302
00:21:25,198 --> 00:21:31,689
I just did it with Brad Pitt!
Oh no, I'm coming! Bang!

303
00:21:31,729 --> 00:21:34,189
I just did it with Ryoko Yonekura!

304
00:21:34,307 --> 00:21:35,453
Oh!

305
00:21:35,493 --> 00:21:38,080
I never fail.

306
00:21:38,507 --> 00:21:40,960
I told you, stop saying that stuff to me!

307
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:42,185
Say it to the audience!

308
00:21:42,225 --> 00:21:45,127
If we're talking about that,
you've been looking down the whole time.

309
00:21:45,167 --> 00:21:46,432
I'm reading the script, okay?

310
00:21:46,472 --> 00:21:48,727
- They'll be there, you know.
- I don't know it yet!

311
00:21:49,194 --> 00:21:51,640
I was getting scared all over again.

312
00:21:52,034 --> 00:21:58,441
I had a feeling that performing this would
lead to something truly terrible.

313
00:21:58,481 --> 00:22:01,281
I just did it with Kate Winslet, too.

314
00:22:01,321 --> 00:22:04,377
When I say "Titanic pose," you do this...

315
00:22:04,417 --> 00:22:05,417
Shohei Uno?

316
00:22:05,418 --> 00:22:06,860
No, no, no! This part!

317
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:15,640
Next Episode Preview

318
00:22:15,670 --> 00:22:17,190
I'm nervous too, you know!

319
00:22:17,193 --> 00:22:19,600
Wait. Hold me.

320
00:22:20,099 --> 00:22:23,679
Is this some kind of punishment game?
Is my whole life a punishment game?

321
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:25,286
I don't think that's true.

322
00:22:25,326 --> 00:22:29,680
It's all my fault. It's all my fault
for not living my own life!
